    "solution": "**Schedule.**\n\n| CC | ALU 1cc | MU 2cc | MU 2cc | FPU 5cc |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 |  | ld $1 | ld $2 |  |\n| 2 | addi R1 | ld $3 |  |  |\n| 4 |  |  |  | addd $2,$2,$3 |\n| 9 |  |  |  | addd $1,$1,$2 |\n| 14 | bnez R1 | sd $1 |  |  |\n| 15 | (delay slot) |  |  |  |\n\n- `ld $1`/`ld $2` at C1 (both MUs), `ld $3` at C2; `addi` at C2 (the store uses `$fp`, not `$R1`, so the index update does not corrupt any address).\n- `addd $2,$2,$3` waits for `$3` (`ld $3`@2 ‚Üí ready @4) ‚Üí **C4**.\n- `addd $1,$1,$2` waits for `$2` (first addd@4, FPU 5cc ‚Üí ready @9) ‚Üí **C9**.\n- `sd $1` waits for `$1` (second addd@9 ‚Üí ready @14) ‚Üí **C14**; `bnez` issues in the same bundle, with its 1-cycle delay slot at C15.\n\n**P1.B ‚Äî performance.** The **critical path** is the dependent chain `ld $2 ‚Üí addd $2 ‚Üí addd $1 ‚Üí sd $1`, i.e. cycles 1 ‚Üí 4 ‚Üí 9 ‚Üí 14. One loop iteration spans **~15 cycles** (the operations finish by C14 and the branch fills its delay slot at C15). **FP ops/cycle** = 2 FP adds / ‚âà15 ‚âà **0.13** ‚Äî the 5cc FPU latency on the dependent add chain dominates, leaving the units idle most cycles.",
    "solutionSource": "exam"
  },
