    "solution": "True dependences: `$1`: I1‚ÜíI3; `$2`: I2‚ÜíI3; `$1`: I3‚ÜíI5; `$2`: I4‚ÜíI5; `$1`: I6‚ÜíI7; `$2`: I5‚ÜíI7. Walk-through:\n- **I1/I2** loads: start 2/3, WB 5/6.\n- **I3** `addd` needs `$1`(5), `$2`(6) ‚Üí start 7, WB 12 (FPU 5cc).\n- **I4** `ld` takes a free load unit ‚Üí start 6, WB 9.\n- **I5** `addd` needs `$1`(I3 WB 12), `$2`(I4 WB 9) ‚Üí start 13, WB 18.\n- **I6** waits for a free **FP reservation station** (I3 frees at WB 12) ‚Üí **issue 13**, start 14, WB 19.\n- **I7** `sd` needs `$1`(I6 WB 19) and the address `$2`(I5 WB 18) ‚Üí start 20, WB 23.\n\nNote how renaming lets I4 (`ld $2`) proceed even though `$2` is still 'live' for I3 ‚Äî the WAR/WAW on `$2`/`$1` are removed; only the true RAW chain and the 2-RS FPU limit (which stalls I6's issue) constrain the schedule.",
